article.headline: Indiana St. 76, Missouri St. 71
article.story: SPRINGFIELD, Mo. -- Harry Marshall scored 19 points, including four straight free throws in the final seconds, to lead Indiana State to a 76-71 win over Missouri State on Saturday. Marshall led all scorers with 19 points as Indiana State (7-19, 5-10 Missouri Valley) watched Missouri State (10-16, 3-12) rally from a nine-point deficit with 7:28 left to take the lead 71-70 with 1:01 left on two Wade Knapp free throws. Two free throws by Jay Tunnell with 42.9 seconds left gave the lead back to Indiana State 72-71. Marshall then hit his free throws in the final four seconds while Missouri State failed to score after Knapp's free throws. Indiana State hit 21 of 22 free throws. Rashad Reed had 14 for Indiana State and Tunnell finished with 13. Jordan Printy added 10. Kyle Weems led Missouri State with 17 and Knapp had 14. Chris Cooks added 12.
